title: AUCC TEMPLATE - 2022
signatory: Bismark Owusu-Baah (Mr.)Head, Admissions & Recruitment For Registrar (AUCC)
template:
ADMISSION TO THE ::program_name PROGRAMME (::admission_title)
    Congratulations!
    I am pleased to inform you that, upon review of your application and, on the basis of your ::cert_condition, you have been offered admission to Level ::start_level of the ::program_name programme for the ::session_year Academic year.
    Holders of Diploma/HND are to submit original copies of their certificate for verification, after which they may be exempted from the university of Ghana required course (offered at AUCC) for one semester. All other applicants will have to pass those required courses to complete their admission.
    Your field of specialisation will be confirmed at the end of Level 200 following an orientation session where you will learn about all the available specialisations and the possible career opportunities available in each specialisation.
  The programme fee per semester is ::fee_amount. However, with a discount of 15%, you are to pay ::discount_amount. Please note that, the discount is for one academic year only. The fee must be paid through Cal Bank in the name of the African University College of Communications (AUCC) into account number ::bank_account at any branch of Cal Bank. After payment, the pay-in-slip must first be presented to the Accounts Officer at AUCC who will issue a receipt, a copy of which must be presented to the appropriate Secretariat of AUCC towards registration.
    Please note that registration will be on ::register_start to ::register_end, and lectures will begin on ::lecture_start. Orientation is on ::orient_start.
    Should you decide to withdraw from the programme within three weeks of registration, the University shall refund your fees to you less an administrative fee of 30%. No refunds will be made for withdrawals after the third week of registration.
    All students are required to obey the rules and regulations of AUCC. A copy of the Student Handbook will be provided to you. Kindly note that AUCCs Weekend School is held on Fridays and Saturdays, and Management reserves the right to change sessions and courses when class sizes are not economically viable.
    All correspondence in relation to your admission should be addressed to the Registrar and should include your reference number as above.
    Congratulations once again. We look forward to personally welcoming you to our campus!
    Yours faithfully,::signature
    ::signatory

title: AUCC TEMPLATE - DEC 2022
template:
ADMISSION TO THE ::program_name PROGRAMME (::admission_title)
    Congratulations!
    I am pleased to inform you that, upon review of your application and, on the basis of your ::cert_condition, you have been offered admission to Level ::start_level of the ::program_name programme for the ::session_year Academic year.
    Holders of Diploma/HND are to submit original copies of their certificate for verification, after which they may be exempted from the university of Ghana required course (offered at AUCC) for one semester. All other applicants will have to pass those required courses to complete their admission.
    Your field of specialisation will be confirmed at the end of Level 200 following an orientation session where you will learn about all the available specialisations and the possible career opportunities available in each specialisation.
  The programme fee per semester is ::fee_amount.You are to pay a commitment fee of One Thousand Ghana Cedis (GH1000.00) by December 20, 2022. The rest of the fees should be paid by January 27, 2023. Additionally, you are to pay a one-time required Ghana Tertiary Education Commission (GTEC) medical examination fee of Three Hundred Ghana Cedis (GH300.00) by Friday February 17, 2023. The fee must be paid through Cal Bank in the name of the African University College of Communications (AUCC) into account number ::bank_account at any branch of Cal Bank. After payment, the pay-in-slip must first be presented to the Accounts Officer at AUCC who will issue a receipt, a copy of which must be presented to the appropriate Secretariat of AUCC towards registration.
    The semester registration for fresh students will be on ::register_start to ::register_end. Lectures will begin on ::lecture_start. All fresh students will participate in an Orientation ceremony to be held on  ::orient_start at the AUCC Auditorium. Matriculation will be on Friday February 17, 2023. 
Your programme shall be either morning, evening or weekends. The weekends run from Fridays 5:00pm to 8:pm and Saturdays from 8:00am to 5:00pm. Management reserves the right to change sessions and courses when class sizes are not economically viable. The Programme is non-residential but there are residential facilities around the campus which could be arranged if you are interested.
   All students are required to obey the rules and regulations of AUCC. A soft copy of the Student Handbook will be provided after registration.
   Your student identification number will be provided on payment of your fees. This will be the number you will use for your examinations and other academic purposes throughout your studies in this University.
AUCC requires that you are declared medically fit by undergoing a medical screening to be conducted on campus from Friday 24 to Saturday 25 February 2023 from 8:00am to 2:00pm.
AUCC reserves the right to cancel this admission offer on detection of false statement of results or withholding of relevant information in relation to this admission.
Should you decide to withdraw from the programme within two weeks of registration, the University shall refund your fees to you less an administrative charge of 30%. No refunds will be made for withdrawals after the third and subsequent weeks of registration.
Congratulations once again and we look forward to personally welcoming you to our campus
All correspondence in relation to your admission which should include your reference number, should be addressed to the:
Registrar - AUCCP.O Box LG510Adabraka, Accra
Yours Sincerely,::signature
::signatory

title: 2023-PG ADMISSION LETTER
template:
GRADUATE ADMISSIONS-WEEKEND PROGRAMME: ::session_year ACADEMIC YEAR, ::program_name 

I have the pleasure to inform you that the African University College of Communications (AUCC) School of Research and Graduate Studies has offered you admission to pursue a One-Year course of study leading to an award of ::program_name.

Your student Identification Number will be provided on payment of fees. This is the number that you will use for your examinations and other academic purposes throughout your studies at AUCC.

The first semester commences on  ::lecture_start. An orientation will be held for all Graduate Students on ::orient_start at the AUCC Auditorium

  The Tuition fee for the ::session_year Academic year is ::fee_amount. This amount is however subject to change. Payment should be made into account number  ::bank_account with account name AUCC Project Work at any Cal Bank branch.

In order that the offer of admission made to you is confirmed, you are to pay a non-refundable commitment fee of GHC 5,600 by ::lecture_start towards the acceptance of this offer.

Registration will be online via the University College website at portal.aucc.edu.gh. You will need your Student Email address and Password to access the University College registration portal. You will be able to register only if you have paid the required percentage of fees as stated above.

The remaining fees should be paid as follows:      a) 30% before end of first semester exams      b) 30% start of second semester registration

Kindly note that the University reserves the right to revoke this offer of admission in the event that discrepancies are detected in the statement and documentation  you submitted as part of your application.

If you accept the terms and conditions of this admission offer, please complete the attached Acceptance Form and submit together with a copy of your your bank pay-in slip to the Graduate School's Secretariat on or before  ::lecture_start

Congratulations.
Yours faithfully,::signature
::signatory
CC: Graduate School Secretariat
